
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `mk_modmap` baraye dorost kardane yek file modmap baraye xmodmap be kar miravad. In dastoor etela'at keyboard ra az X server migirad va yek file ra ba estelahate lazem baraye taghir dadane raftare keyboard misazad.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `mk_modmap -verbose` --> 🗣️ Namayesh peygham-haye bishtar dar hale ejra.
    🔹 `mk_modmap -output filename` --> 📤 Save natije be yek file khass be jaye stdout.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ mk_modmap

    🔹 Sakhte yek file modmap dar stdout.

    $ mk_modmap -output .Xmodmap

    🔹 Sakhte yek file modmap be name .Xmodmap dar directory hoom.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ mk_modmap > .Xmodmap

    🔹 In command file modmap ra misazad va natije ra dar yek file be name ".Xmodmap" save mikonad. Baad az an, mitavanid `xmodmap .Xmodmap` ra ejra konid ta taghirat ra amal konid.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `mk_modmap` command is used to create a modmap file for xmodmap. This command retrieves keyboard information from the X server and generates a file with the necessary terms to modify the keyboard behavior.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `mk_modmap -verbose` --> 🗣️ Display more messages during execution.
    🔹 `mk_modmap -output filename` --> 📤 Save the output to a specific file instead of stdout.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ mk_modmap

    🔹 Generates a modmap file to standard output.

    $ mk_modmap -output .Xmodmap

    🔹 Generates a modmap file named .Xmodmap in the home directory.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ mk_modmap > .Xmodmap

    🔹 This command creates a modmap file and saves the output to a file named ".Xmodmap". After that, you can run `xmodmap .Xmodmap` to apply the changes.
